<paragraph base="F16124232" principles="no" id="IAS28_26"><paranum>26</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 28"/><data name="paranum" value="26"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS28_P0085">Many of the procedures that are appropriate for the application of the <xref base="F16124092" href="IAS28_3.dita#IAS28_3/IAS28_P0018">equity method<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0105"/></ph></xref> are similar to the consolidation procedures described in <xref base="F16160794" href="../ifrs10/IFRS10_TOC.dita#IFRS10_TOC0001" id="IAS28_X0150">IFRS 10</xref>. Furthermore, the concepts underlying the procedures used in accounting for the acquisition of a <xref base="F16125891" href="../ifrs10/IFRS10_APPA.dita#IFRS10_APPA/IFRS10_TE0012">subsidiary<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0360"/></ph></xref> are also adopted in accounting for the acquisition of an investment in an <xref base="F16124075" href="IAS28_3.dita#IAS28_3/IAS28_P0016">associate<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0018"/></ph></xref> or a <xref base="F16124099" href="IAS28_3.dita#IAS28_3/IAS28_P0021">joint venture<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0211"/></ph></xref>.</p></body></paragraph>